    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review decision to fund replacement of The Royal Preston Hospital",
        "additional_details": "The Government said it would build new Hospitals but closing down existing ones is unacceptable. The Royal Preston Hospital is a perfectly working Hospital and more investment should he made in currently run Hospitals than wasting money on building new ones.\r\n \r\nThe Government should review its decision to fund the replacement of The Royal Preston Hospital, and instead consider providing additional funding for the running of this hospital.",
        "background": "The Royal Preston Hospital is the lifeline of Preston it serves Preston very well and it should not be closed down. We don't want an out of town hospital in a remote location.",
